# ~/.config/hwe/packages.lst — the packages YOU want on this machine.
#
# One package per line, '#' starts a comment — the same format as HWE's own
# lists in pkg/. `hwe install` installs them, `hwe update` offers to install
# what is missing, and `hwe doctor` reports them alongside HWE's lists.
#
# This file is yours and lives outside the repository: pkg/ stays HWE's answer
# to "what does this environment need", and yours never collides on a pull.
# Packages listed here are installed with pacman — put AUR ones in
# packages-aur.lst next to this file.

# thunderbird
# mpv
# libreoffice-fresh
